STRICT_FORMAT_CLEANUP_RULES

Status: Mandatory
Scope: renderer.js (and any future UI renderer modules)
Skill Gate: Always run `pre-assign-naming-gate` before assigning or renaming variables/objects/functions.

Rule 1: Top-level registries and config maps must use UPPER_SNAKE.
- Required format: A_B_C style with uppercase letters and underscores.
- Examples:
  - MOD_ALIAS
  - MOD_FUNCTION_GROUPS
  - REQUIRED_MODULE_FUNCTIONS
  - APP_STATE, APP_STORE, APP_CFG
  - PAGE_NAMESPACE, DOM_ELEMENT_MAP

Rule 2: Repeated literal patterns must be extracted into explicit PATTERN_* constants.
- Required format:
  - PATTERN_<DOMAIN>_<NAME>
- Use Object.freeze(...) for static pattern maps.
- Examples:
  - PATTERN_ALIAS_KEY
  - PATTERN_UNIVERSE_EDGE_MODE
  - PATTERN_UNIVERSE_EDGE_ACTIONS

Rule 3: Repeated action bindings must be deduped into a single pattern array.
- Store as tuples and iterate.
- Required tuple format:
  - [elementKey, modeKey]
- Example use cases:
  - syncControls() state toggles
  - bindActionElement() edge-mode bindings

Rule 4: Alias/group namespace objects must remain stable and centralized.
- Runtime namespace aliases:
  - G_APP, G_RT, G_PAGE, G_DOM, G_UNI, G_UNI_FX
- No chained mutation aliases that corrupt paths (example of forbidden pattern: G_UNI.G_APP.c...)

Rule 5: Validation gate is required after every cleanup pass.
- Required checks:
  - npm run lint --silent
  - npm test --silent


TOOL / FUNCTION TEMPLATE

Name: applyStrictFormatCleanup
Purpose: enforce naming + pattern extraction + deduped mapping rules

Template:

function applyStrictFormatCleanup({
  topLevelRegistryNames,
  patternMapNames,
  dedupedActionMaps
}) {
  // 1) Assert top-level registry names are UPPER_SNAKE
  topLevelRegistryNames.forEach((name) => {
    if (!/^[A-Z][A-Z0-9_]*$/.test(name)) {
      throw new Error(`Invalid top-level registry format: ${name}`);
    }
  });

  // 2) Assert pattern constants follow PATTERN_* naming
  patternMapNames.forEach((name) => {
    if (!/^PATTERN_[A-Z0-9_]+$/.test(name)) {
      throw new Error(`Invalid pattern constant name: ${name}`);
    }
  });

  // 3) Assert deduped action maps use [elementKey, modeKey] tuples
  dedupedActionMaps.forEach((map) => {
    map.forEach((row) => {
      if (!Array.isArray(row) || row.length !== 2) {
        throw new Error("Action map rows must be [elementKey, modeKey]");
      }
      const [elementKey, modeKey] = row;
      if (typeof elementKey !== "string" || typeof modeKey !== "string") {
        throw new Error("Action map keys must be strings");
      }
    });
  });

  return true;
}


FOLLOW TEMPLATE (PER PASS)

1) Normalize names:
- convert top-level registry/config names to UPPER_SNAKE.

2) Extract literal patterns:
- pull repeated strings into PATTERN_* constants.

3) Dedupe action mappings:
- convert repeated bind/toggle statements into iterable tuple maps.

4) Verify no invalid chained aliases:
- disallow accidental paths such as G_UNI.G_APP.c.

5) Run mandatory validation:
- npm run lint --silent
- npm test --silent
